<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1724,2003]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">
Type data: This species was described based on an undetermined number of females collected in 
<collectingCountry box="[1238,1310,1724,1750]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. There was found a single female of this species in 
<collectionCode box="[618,724,1760,1786]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">OUMNH</collectionCode>
with original Lepeletier’s labels being here designated as the 
<typeStatus box="[151,257,1796,1822]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">lectotype</typeStatus>
. The specimen has the following data label: [circular label with red margin] Type [printed]\ 
<taxonomicName authority="Lepel." authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">Centris ferruginea</emphasis>
Lepel.
</taxonomicName>
<specimenCount box="[325,346,1833,1859]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
Brasilia [handwritten] (
<collectionCode box="[618,731,1832,1858]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">OUMNH</collectionCode>
). According to the original description, the 
<typeStatus box="[1223,1326,1832,1858]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">lectotype</typeStatus>
belonged to Dejean’s collection. Unfortunately, it is strongly damaged, with the eyes and metasoma missing.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="13.[151,1437,1724,2003]" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">
All specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Lepeletier" authorityYear="1841" box="[398,550,1904,1931]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Centris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="13" pageNumber="36" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="ferruginea">
<emphasis box="[398,417,1905,1931]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">C</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[432,550,1904,1930]" italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">ferruginea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found at 
<collectionCode box="[659,739,1905,1931]" country="USA" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/3kvn-7rck" name="Princeton University" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">MNHP</collectionCode>
were collected before the description of the species and none of them in 
<collectingCountry box="[273,345,1940,1966]" name="Brazil" pageId="13" pageNumber="36">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
